==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*murnanan''.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[mornan]], Old High German [[mornen|mornēn]], Old Norse [[morna]], Gothic [[𐌼𐌰𐌿𐍂𐌽𐌰𐌽]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈmʊrnan/}}

===Verb===
'''murnan''' (class III strong: ''3 singular preterite'' '''[[mearn]]''', ''preterite plural'' '''[[murnon]]''')

# to [[care]] for, [[worry]] about
# to be [[sorrowful]], to [[mourn]]

===Descendants===
*English: [[mourn]]

